Data Engineer		Picwell		Philadelphia, PA, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong>Job Description<br /><br />We are looking for a data-centric software engineer to help build our next-generation data platform. You will be responsible for designing and developing automated systems to simulate health outcomes for millions of people using large datasets and manage data acquisition &amp; transformations of our data feeds at scale.<br /><br />Our data platform serves as the basis for Picwell’s advanced analytics. We are designing modern ETL pipelines to process information using open source tooling (Python, Scala) from multiple sources and data stores.<br /><br />Our engineering culture is one committed to high code quality through peer review and collaborative development. Our ideal candidate demonstrates an ability to learn and deploy new technologies, an interest in using technology to solve societal problems, and good communication and people skills. <br /><br /><strong>Qualifications<br /></strong><ul><li>Two years software development experience</li><li>Bachelors degree (or higher) in Computer Science or related field</li><li>Experience with a dynamic scripting language like Python or Ruby, and *nix command-line tools</li><li>Experience with SQL and relational database design</li><li>Experience developing and deploying modern ETL pipelines with open-source tools</li><li>Familiarity with test-driven design, and a strong commitment to code quality</li><li>Experience with a distributed version control system like git or mercurial<br /></li></ul><li>*If you meet 70% of these, we encourage you to apply!<br /><br /></li>Additional Information<br /><br />Pluses<br /><ul><li>Experience with distributed computing frameworks, e.g. Hadoop, Spark</li><li>Experience with Amazon Web Services (RDS, RedShift, S3, EC2, EMR, Data Pipeline)</li><li>Familiarity with statistical and data analysis programs such as Pandas, R, Stata</li><li>Familiarity with healthcare data (public data sets, claims data)</li><li>Familiarity with functional programming (e.g. Scala)</li><li>Experience working with remote teams</li><li>Experience with Agile methodologies and Scrum</li></ul>Benefits<br /><ul><li>Health insurance benefits</li><li>MacBook Pro + budget for accessories</li><li>Flexible schedules</li><li>Thursday team lunches</li><li>Team outings and fun!</li><li>Slack<br /><br /></li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Picwell is an early-stage healthcare startup developing technology to help consumers navigate the complexities of choice in health insurance. <br /><br />The lack of consumer-friendly recommendations in health insurance leads to poor decision making, which translates into higher personal expense, lower satisfaction and billions of dollars of waste in the healthcare system. By using predictive analytics and machine learning, our SaaS platform delivers to consumers, for the first time, truly personalized and objective recommendations on insurance plans, tailored to their individual needs and preferences for protection and cost.<br /><br />Founded by leading academics in the fields of healthcare and behavioral economics at the University of Pennsylvania, Picwell is a small, fun-loving team that is looking to expand!</div>